body:
Hi,
  A string Q is used, its elements are processed inside a foreach, so far it works. Now, foreach element in this string Q, say we want to compare the length of the string and do some processing, Icarus breaks. 

Minmalist test:

```verilog
module m;

  string m_argv [$];

  initial begin
    m_argv.push_back ("str0");

    foreach (m_argv[i]) begin
      if(m_argv[i].len() >= 2) begin
        $display ("LARGE: %0d", lv_len);
      end
  
    end
  end
endmodule : m

```

```log
bb.sv:9: error: Scope index expression is not constant: i
bb.sv:9: error: Scope index expression is not constant: i
bb.sv:9: error: No function named `m_argv[i].len' found in this context (m.$ivl_foreach0).
bb.sv:9: error: Unable to elaborate condition expression.
4 error(s) during elaboration.
```

I tried breaking the code to get individual string, get it length, compare, that works as below.

```verilog
module m;

  string m_argv [$];
  string lv_s;
  int lv_len;

  initial begin
    m_argv.push_back ("str0");
    m_argv.push_back ("str1");
    m_argv.push_back ("str0123");

    foreach (m_argv[i]) begin
      $display ("%s", m_argv[i]);
      lv_s = m_argv[i];
      lv_len = lv_s.len();
      $display ("%0d", lv_len);
      if(lv_len >= 2) begin
        $display ("LARGE: %0d", lv_len);
      end
   
    end
  end
endmodule : m


```

